This is a python3  directory. It holds code for the bms_async_server

The code here may be run in a host terminal with virtual environment.
The virtual env must include sqlite3. 
bms_async_server's purpose is to:
  1. Translate msgs from clients: Adc_async_client and Gui_async_client setting attributes on server variables as needed.
  2. Route cmds to the DBI (DatabaseInterface)  or one of the clients: Adc_async_client, Gui_async_client
  3. compute summary data from Adc_clients A2D data to complete the BMS record for storage and send, 
  4. delegate to the DBI to store the augmented BMS record to the BMS table 
  5. delegate to the DBI to store A2D data to the A2D table managing the bms_id to ensure that A2S data maps correctly to the BMS record. 
  6. Format msgs to return cmd responses to the Gui_async_client.
  7. Allow connections from both clients and manage the msg traffic correctly.

Voltage taps on the battery cells provides three channels: One cell, Two cells, Three cells.
bms_async_server will compute status of each of three cells using subtraction.
The Gui_async_client commands are listed in the table below.
The bms_async_server maintains the msgid so that responses can be mapped back to requests.
There may be many hosts that perform the Gui_async_client functions: mobile, desktop, laptop, etc.
bms_async_server may need to modify msg response depending on the display
device. TBD
The Server receives the commands via asyncio from the Gui_asyncio_client and forwards them to Adc_async_client.
A measurment command (100) will result in 3 measurement reports, each with voltage measurements for ( One cell , Two Cells, Three Cells)
A calibration command(200) will be for a single channel and will contain the Truth value, called "vin" for input voltage . 
A calibration command will result in one calibration_report(201) msg sent to the Server with "vin" embedded along with normal samples and neccesary fields.
F
r the Start_Periodic cmd,  Gui_async_client will pass two attributes thru the Server to the Adc_async_client, Start_Periodic.period and Start_Periodic.repetitions.
A measurement(100) and a calibration(200) command will vary in two ways: the type ('m','c') and vin = [0, truthValue], where 'm' means measure and 'c' means calibrate.
The time between cmd and response is estimated to be ~5 seconds.
A small amount of time will be expended in translating incoming msgs and formatting outgoing messages.
The bms_async_server will respond to Gui_async_client commands by delegating cmds to the DBI to update database tables as needed.
Reports from the Server on database tables will include the id to facilitate updates.
The Configuration of the App will be versioned. 
The Gui_async_client will set version so that tables are in sync with the current configuration.
The server will set the version attribute when Gui_async_client sends it to the server.

Summary:
1. Code must run in python3 to allow for larger frameworks in virtual environments.
2. Server must be able to translate cmds and process reports sent via json and asyncio
4. Future work could allow Gui_async_client to specify changes in the number of samples, sample_rate, etc, which are frozen for now.
5. Future work could require the Server to adapt to fulfill the needed changes.
5. Process latency estimated to be very small.
6. Msg sizes should be less than 1kb.


Commands (codes) that the Gui_async_client can send:
100, 150, 152, 175, 200, 300, 310, 350, 360, 370 

Delegated to the database_interface.py
Requestor must embed the required argslist, [...],  in the msg along with the code.
Following functions can be activated from database_interface.call_function(code:int, arglist: list)
 
   functions_dict  = dict()                                              # argslist
        functions_dict[150]= self.list_records                           # ([ chan, type])
        functions_dict[152]= self.get_a2d_samples                        # ([bms_id])
        functions_dict[300]= self.save_config                            # ([cfg_id, msg:Config])
        functions_dict[310]= self.load_config                            # ([chan] )
        functions_dict[350]= self.update_lut_pair                        # ([ chan, id, vm, vin] )    
        functions_dict[360]= self.get_lut                                # ([chan] )
        functions_dict[370]= self.get_lut_timestamp                      # ([ chan ])
        self.functions_dict = functions_dict
# This functions_dict is part of database_interface.py
